  <summary>In a time of starvation, a survivalist lives off a small plot of land hidden deep in forest. When two women seeking food and shelter discover his farm, he finds his existence threatened.</summary>
  <reviews>
    <item index="0">
      <text>You'll leave completely rapt.</text>
      <source>Time Out</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>https://www.timeout.com/us/film/the-survivalist</link>
      <author>Joshua Rothkopf</author>
    </item>
    <item index="1">
      <text>eerie and masterful ... as riveting as it is morally confounding.</text>
      <source>Los Angeles Times</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-mini-survivalist-review-20170518-story.html</link>
      <author>Katie Walsh</author>
    </item>
    <item index="2">
      <text>Impressively lean and rigidly controlled, "The Survivalist" achieves, at times, the primitive allure of a silent movie.</text>
      <source>New York Times</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>https://www.nytimes.com/2017/05/17/movies/the-survivalist-review.html?_r=0</link>
      <author>Jeannette Catsoulis</author>
    </item>
    <item index="3">
      <text>Fingleton's spare, striking debut feature takes a minimalist approach to the post-apocalyptic thriller.</text>
      <source>AV Club</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.avclub.com/review/survivalist-post-apocalyptic-action-its-most-minim-255423</link>
      <author>Katie Rife</author>
    </item>
    <item index="4">
      <text>Both dire and oddly poetic.</text>
      <source>Village Voice</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.villagevoice.com/2017/05/17/tracking-shots-this-week-in-film-2/</link>
      <author>Craig D. Lindsey</author>
    </item>
    <item index="5">
      <text>A post-apocalyptic drama as stripped-down as its title suggests, The Survivalist envisions end times in which each encounter with a new human entails a hard calculus of risk versus advantage.</text>
      <source>Hollywood Reporter</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/survivalist-tribeca-review-789013</link>
      <author>John DeFore</author>
    </item>
    <item index="6">
      <text>A canny study of trust and loyalty.</text>
      <source>Time Out</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.timeout.com/london/film/the-survivalist</link>
      <author>David Clack</author>
    </item>
